were killed in the collapse.

23:17.079 --> 23:19.958
And although they've been branded
the "lucky eight"...

23:20.115 --> 23:24.222
...the surviving employees
new face an uncertain future.

23:44.072 --> 23:45.312
NATHAN:
Hey, guys.

23:45.474 --> 23:46.578
MOLLY:
Hey.

23:46.741 --> 23:47.811
PETER:
Hey.

23:49.311 --> 23:52.656
Anybody know
when this thing's supposed to start?

23:52.814 --> 23:56.159
When Dennis gets here, I guess.

23:57.919 --> 23:59.592
That agent still hounding you?

24:00.155 --> 24:04.262
No. You heard the news,
it was natural causes.

24:04.993 --> 24:06.597
Yeah, more like supernatural.

24:08.163 --> 24:10.871
How you holding up? I tried calling.

24:11.032 --> 24:14.377
No, yeah, I saw. I was just tired.

24:16.404 --> 24:17.644
ISAAC:
So?

24:19.274 --> 24:20.981
How did you explain it?

24:23.845 --> 24:25.153
I didn't.

24:26.348 --> 24:27.383
I couldn't.

24:27.549 --> 24:29.324
Sam, there had to be a reason.

24:29.484 --> 24:31.896
Heh. That is exactly
what the agent kept saying.

24:36.124 --> 24:39.537
Whatever answer you're lacking for,
I don't have it.

24:39.694 --> 24:42.038
Yeah, Sam's right.
It doesn't matter how it happened.

24:42.197 --> 24:45.576
We should all just put it behind us
and be grateful we're still alive.

24:48.470 --> 24:50.848
Definitely beats the alternative, right?

24:51.072 --> 24:52.915
DENNIS:
I look out at the faces today...

24:53.074 --> 24:56.681
...and I see family members, friends.

24:57.546 --> 25:02.086
But the people that left us on the bridge
that day, they were more than that.

25:02.717 --> 25:04.754
People like Jennifer Alcott...

25:06.955 --> 25:08.366
...Chris Boylan...

25:10.091 --> 25:11.229
...David Buckler.

25:12.494 --> 25:14.496
Maybe you worked next to them.

25:14.663 --> 25:16.404
Maybe you worked for them.

25:16.565 --> 25:20.342
But we all worked with them, huh?

25:20.535 --> 25:23.607
Who can forget Trevor Wino's smile?

25:26.241 --> 25:27.777
Or Isaac Palmer.

25:28.610 --> 25:29.987
Did he just say my name?

25:30.145 --> 25:31.453
[OLIVIA SNORTS]

25:31.613 --> 25:33.593
-That's not funny.
-I know, I'm sorry.

25:33.748 --> 25:36.661
I just get weird with tragedies. I'm sorry.

25:38.687 --> 25:39.893
[WHISPERS]
I see dead people.

25:40.055 --> 25:41.466
[OLIVIA LAUGHING]

25:41.623 --> 25:42.897
Guys.

25:52.400 --> 25:53.606
Death...

25:56.004 --> 25:57.574
...doesn't like to be cheated.

25:58.240 --> 25:59.514
Excuse me?

25:59.774 --> 26:01.117
What's that supposed to mean?

26:05.780 --> 26:08.954
You all just be careful now.

26:09.117 --> 26:11.256
PETER:
Okay. Thanks for the advice!

26:12.320 --> 26:13.458
Creepy guy.

26:13.622 --> 26:16.626
[BLUDWORTH WHISTLING
"LEANING ON THE EVERLASTING ARMS"]

26:36.311 --> 26:39.417
COOK:
How's that foie gras, Sam? Waiting on you.

26:48.757 --> 26:50.168
[TERRY POISON'S "BALLROOM"
PLAYING]

26:50.325 --> 26:53.795
Wasted like a drunk
She drank, drunk, drunk

26:53.962 --> 26:55.703
Stop it

26:55.864 --> 26:57.309
It's not forgotten

26:58.166 --> 26:59.201
COOK 1:
Thanks.

26:59.367 --> 27:00.573
COOK 2:
Got my dessert?

27:05.974 --> 27:07.248
[MIKE CLEARS THROAT]

27:08.710 --> 27:10.018
What's the matter with it?

27:10.178 --> 27:12.385
Said it was flat. No flavor.

27:13.615 --> 27:15.561
-Do they want something else?
MIKE: Yeah.

27:15.717 --> 27:16.889
The check.

27:19.788 --> 27:21.768
Let me taste it.

27:27.162 --> 27:30.632
The customer is an asshole.
The bourguignon is good.

27:42.911 --> 27:44.549
MOLLY:
Hold on.

27:57.425 --> 27:58.768
You mind if I came in?

27:58.927 --> 28:00.838
Yeah. Sure.

28:11.005 --> 28:12.040
Thanks.

28:12.207 --> 28:14.016
I thought you'd be working tonight.

28:14.175 --> 28:17.418
Yeah. You know,
I worked the first shift, but...

28:18.513 --> 28:20.686
...there was something else I needed to do.

28:22.784 --> 28:25.458
[WHISTLING]

28:26.788 --> 28:28.028
-Can l...?
-Oh.

28:28.189 --> 28:30.829
Yeah. Sure, go ahead.

29:14.869 --> 29:17.440
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

29:24.646 --> 29:25.750
Thank you.

29:27.348 --> 29:28.520
Listen ....

29:30.218 --> 29:32.721
When everything started going down
on that bridge...

29:35.990 --> 29:38.664
...the only thing I thought about
was you.

29:39.861 --> 29:41.807
Getting you to safety.

29:42.430 --> 29:46.003
You are the only thing
I care about, Molly.

29:48.803 --> 29:51.374
Whatever's wrong, I can fix it.

29:51.539 --> 29:53.951
You haven't done anything wrong.

29:55.043 --> 29:56.989
Then, what? What is it?

29:58.513 --> 29:59.548
Paris.

29:59.848 --> 30:01.327
We talked about that.

30:01.483 --> 30:06.364
I'm not going to uproot my life,
leave you, for that jab.

30:06.521 --> 30:09.024
But it's the only thing
you've ever dreamed of.

30:11.793 --> 30:13.739
Life is too short, Sam.

30:13.895 --> 30:16.466
You have to go after what you love.

30:17.465 --> 30:18.705
I am.

30:23.304 --> 30:25.215
You should take the jab.

30:27.141 --> 30:29.417
Go to Paris.

30:45.894 --> 30:47.430
-Hey.
CANDICE: Hey.

30:47.595 --> 30:49.006
What's the matter?

30:49.531 --> 30:52.705
I don't know. I'm not ready.
I don't feel ready.

30:52.867 --> 30:56.337
It's been really hard to concentrate
after everything.

30:57.372 --> 30:58.680
Yeah? Are you sure?

30:59.374 --> 31:00.682
Yeah.

31:00.842 --> 31:03.755
Because this is the last practice
before the championship.

31:04.212 --> 31:06.419
And it's your last practice
of your college career.

31:06.581 --> 31:08.322
CANDICE:
I know, but ....

31:09.918 --> 31:12.159
I think you get this.

31:13.454 --> 31:15.195
-Really?
PETER: Yeah.

31:16.057 --> 31:18.162
I mean, you love it out there.

31:19.727 --> 31:21.229
Okay. You're right.

31:21.396 --> 31:23.637
And besides, coach would kill me. Heh.

31:23.798 --> 31:25.368
Yeah.

31:25.533 --> 31:26.637
Here.

31:28.703 --> 31:30.239
Thanks.

31:30.405 --> 31:31.577
Come here.

31:34.142 --> 31:35.348
Bye.

31:37.111 --> 31:38.886
PETER:
You get this.

31:48.623 --> 31:51.502
MAN 1: You have to get a little more speed.
You gotta hit that follow-up.

31:55.863 --> 31:59.208
GIRL 1: I'm sore from the back extensions.
GIRL 2: Really?

32:05.073 --> 32:06.643
Okay, seriously, this is stupid.

32:06.808 --> 32:09.311
They've gotta make it cooler
or we're gonna pass out.

32:09.477 --> 32:11.013
They're working on it.

32:11.179 --> 32:13.250
CANDICE:
Well, they Should have it fixed by new.

32:13.414 --> 32:16.395
[BEEPING]

32:36.904 --> 32:39.282
COACH:
Come on, Candice. You're up.

32:49.183 --> 32:50.958
PETER:
Come on, Candice. You get this.

33:17.145 --> 33:20.285
COACH:
Candice, now.

33:26.788 --> 33:29.826
MAN 1:
Really strong value on this.

33:41.102 --> 33:43.013
GIRL 3:
Hey, coach! How was that?

34:02.790 --> 34:05.794
MAN 1: I wanna see you guys
run the routine all the way through once.

34:24.145 --> 34:25.179
-That's good.
-Whew.

34:25.346 --> 34:27.382
MAN 1:
All right, Janine next. Let's go.

34:27.547 --> 34:29.858
Let's go, ladies, and drink water.

34:34.789 --> 34:35.824
That's it.

34:36.290 --> 34:38.292
Every time, Candice.

34:43.331 --> 34:45.072
-There you go.
-Thanks.

34:45.233 --> 34:47.179
COACH:
Nicely done, Candice.

34:52.005 --> 34:53.542
Okay, go to bars.

34:53.708 --> 34:55.847
WOMAN:
Come on. Hit the floor. You can do it.

34:58.346 --> 35:00.257
PETER:
Go hard this time, Candice.

35:01.182 --> 35:02.627
Let's be aggressive.

35:03.885 --> 35:07.492
COACH:
Here we go, Candice. Stay loose.

35:08.389 --> 35:10.096
MAN 2:
Okay, Porter, it's your turn.

35:11.359 --> 35:12.963
Stay focused.

35:14.362 --> 35:15.636
MAN 3:
Good.

35:21.702 --> 35:23.477
COACH:
Looking good, Candice.

35:54.836 --> 35:56.975
[SCREAMING]

36:01.142 --> 36:03.622
[YELLING]

36:04.645 --> 36:05.680
[GIRLS SCREAMING]

36:05.847 --> 36:07.349
Candice? Candice?!

36:07.515 --> 36:09.825
GIRL 4: Oh, what happened?
MAN 1: Don't touch her.

36:09.984 --> 36:11.691
COACH:
Someone call 911.

36:11.853 --> 36:12.888
Candice?

36:15.022 --> 36:17.400
[AMBULANCE SIREN BEEPS]

36:20.394 --> 36:22.396
[CHATTERING]

36:34.308 --> 36:36.083
Peter.

36:50.324 --> 36:52.167
I came as soon as I heard.

36:55.830 --> 36:57.468
She was doing great.

37:00.067 --> 37:03.514
She was almost finished with her routine
and then ....

37:10.645 --> 37:12.522
Why did it happen?

37:15.249 --> 37:17.729
This doesn't make any sense.

37:17.885 --> 37:19.592
I don't know, man.

37:22.890 --> 37:25.393
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry, Peter.

37:39.006 --> 37:40.986
Let's just go, Sam.

37:55.256 --> 37:56.735
Hey.

37:57.191 --> 37:58.966
How's it going?

37:59.994 --> 38:01.871
It's weird.

38:02.930 --> 38:04.500
Being here, I mean.

38:06.634 --> 38:08.443
It's just so quiet.

38:09.804 --> 38:12.785
Yeah, well, Dennis had all the calls
rerouted to corporate.

38:13.708 --> 38:16.814
Yeah, well, it's depressing.

38:20.314 --> 38:23.295
Holy crap. Did you guys
get your bereavement pay yet?

38:27.955 --> 38:29.093
Hey, what's he doing here?

38:29.924 --> 38:32.336
I think he just needed the distraction.

38:32.526 --> 38:33.971
Yeah.

38:34.929 --> 38:36.875
Yeah, that's a bummer about Candice.

38:37.665 --> 38:40.111
Guess we all should have seen
that coming.

38:42.603 --> 38:43.775
What?

38:43.938 --> 38:47.818
You see the crazy shit those gymnasts do.
I'm surprised it doesn't happen more often.

38:49.210 --> 38:51.486
MAN [OVER SPEAKERPHONE]:
Once you've handled the e-mail...

38:51.645 --> 38:54.524
...you'll need to deactivate all the key cards
of the deceased employees.

38:54.682 --> 38:56.218
Instructions are in your binder.

38:56.384 --> 38:59.661
Well, shouldn't that be the jab
of the facility manager?

39:00.388 --> 39:02.459
The facility manager's dead.

39:03.157 --> 39:04.227
[SIGHS]

39:04.392 --> 39:06.394
Dennis, you want me to fly someone
up there?

39:06.594 --> 39:07.902
No, no, I get it.

39:15.603 --> 39:16.741
Aw, Debbie.

39:22.676 --> 39:24.849
You were so naughty.

39:34.188 --> 39:35.565
[COINS JINGLING]

39:38.726 --> 39:40.034
Fuck it.

39:47.334 --> 39:49.143
Robert, my man.

39:58.546 --> 39:59.854
Ow.

40:02.450 --> 40:03.793
Shit.

40:10.424 --> 40:12.665
You shouldn't have, buddy.

40:24.038 --> 40:25.540
Hey, man, what are you doing up here?

40:25.706 --> 40:29.279
Had to get off the factory floor, man.
Roy's driving me crazy.

40:29.810 --> 40:32.654
So, uh, who wants one?

40:32.813 --> 40:33.917
Where'd you get these?

40:34.081 --> 40:38.223
I stole it out of Roy's truck.
Ha, ha. It's good, right? Ha, ha.

40:38.385 --> 40:39.887
I get something better.

40:40.521 --> 40:41.932
OLIVIA:
Ooh, nice one.

40:42.089 --> 40:43.625
Yeah, count me in.

40:44.592 --> 40:46.003
Are you sure you wanna share that?

40:46.727 --> 40:51.198
If I don't, I'll end up drinking it alone,
which is just sad.

40:51.799 --> 40:53.938
Well, this day just got way more fun.

41:06.647 --> 41:09.423
No, I did call you.

41:09.617 --> 41:13.224
Of course. I just called you
right now, didn't I?

41:13.487 --> 41:16.195
Because I really do
wanna take you out again.

41:16.357 --> 41:19.361
Yeah, yeah, we'll do, like, a nice
romantic dinner.

41:19.527 --> 41:22.007
You know,
somewhere maybe outside the city.

41:22.163 --> 41:23.437
Hold up.

41:26.734 --> 41:28.975
You know what? I gotta go.

41:29.136 --> 41:31.309
No, no, no. I'm not blowing you off.

41:31.472 --> 41:35.147
Hey, listen. Hey, who's my girl, Kimber?

41:35.309 --> 41:37.084
Amber, yes, that's what I said.

41:37.244 --> 41:38.279
Excuse me.

41:44.251 --> 41:49.360
Amber? Amber, I'm sorry, wait a second.
Is that weird sound on your end or mi--?

41:49.523 --> 41:54.233
Sorry about that. My, uh, sister
tends to get a little chatty sometimes.

41:54.395 --> 41:56.238
-Uh-huh.
-Uh-huh.

41:56.397 --> 42:00.368
So tell me about stress relief.

42:00.534 --> 42:04.175
And what does this really get me?

42:04.338 --> 42:07.046
This covers a session
for two different physical therapies.

42:07.241 --> 42:09.517
Like massage therapy?

42:10.344 --> 42:12.620
Erotic massage?

42:14.048 --> 42:17.689
This is a family operation.
Everyone on staff is professional.

42:17.851 --> 42:21.822
Hey, that's great. I prefer a professional.
In fact, you know what? I kind of demand it.

42:21.989 --> 42:27.701
I'm just trying to clarify, though, that this
professional experience ends, uh...

42:29.730 --> 42:30.765
[WHISPERS]
...happy.

42:33.834 --> 42:35.836
I know exactly what you need.

42:36.003 --> 42:38.040
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
Oh, I'm sure you do.

42:38.205 --> 42:40.378
-Follow me, please.
-I'd love to.

42:40.541 --> 42:41.918
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

42:42.076 --> 42:43.680
Slow down there a little bit.

42:43.844 --> 42:46.723
Yeah. Yeah, you have
a lovely little canter.

42:49.483 --> 42:50.553
[ISAAC CHUCKLING]

42:50.718 --> 42:52.891
Yum yum, dim sum.

42:53.053 --> 42:54.430
Hold up there a second.

42:54.588 --> 42:57.068
All right, these are solid.
Just making sure.

42:57.224 --> 42:59.397
Tend to be a bit noisy,
if you know what I mean.

43:03.764 --> 43:07.712
Ha, ha. Yo, Buddha.
Slow down on the rice cakes.

43:12.006 --> 43:13.917
-Just close your eyes.
-Mm-hm.

43:14.074 --> 43:15.348
-Relax.
-Ooh.

43:15.509 --> 43:20.185
And someone will be in
to service you soon.

43:20.347 --> 43:22.258
Oh, yeah.

43:32.893 --> 43:34.566
[MOANS]

43:34.728 --> 43:36.605
Oh, yeah.

43:36.764 --> 43:38.107
Feels dynamite.

43:38.265 --> 43:42.213
No, no. You're going the wrong way there,
little lady.

43:42.369 --> 43:44.076
[CHO SPEAKING IN CHINESE]

43:45.072 --> 43:46.415
Oh.

43:47.207 --> 43:49.585
Wait a second, what happened
to the younger version of you?

43:53.414 --> 43:56.122
Okay, I'm sorry.
Do you came with subtitles?

43:56.283 --> 43:57.318
[IN CHINESE]

43:57.484 --> 43:59.361
Maybe I should go.

44:00.120 --> 44:02.430
Don't know what that means. No idea. Yep.

44:02.589 --> 44:04.068
Ow!

44:04.224 --> 44:05.259
Fuck!

44:06.994 --> 44:10.066
No, no, that's okay.
That's okay, I'm all right.

44:10.230 --> 44:11.402
Holy shit, you're strong.

44:11.565 --> 44:12.669
CHO:

44:12.833 --> 44:14.210
What are you doing? Ow.

44:14.368 --> 44:15.779
You're a little aggressive.

44:16.837 --> 44:19.340
What's "capay"?
I don't know what that means.

44:19.573 --> 44:22.110
I don't want a "foo-hay." No "foo-hay." Aah!

44:22.276 --> 44:23.380
[SCREAMS]

44:23.544 --> 44:26.388
[ISAAC SOBBING]

44:27.247 --> 44:29.420
ALL:
Cheers.

44:30.551 --> 44:31.859
OLIVIA:
Mm.

44:33.654 --> 44:36.658
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

44:37.925 --> 44:39.097
Shit, that's my ride.

44:39.259 --> 44:40.829
Shit. I gotta go.

44:41.261 --> 44:42.763
SAM:
Leaving more for us.

44:44.498 --> 44:45.670
[GLASS BREAKS]

44:50.938 --> 44:53.179
SAM:
All right, well, more for me.

44:53.340 --> 44:54.478
All right, bye.

44:54.908 --> 44:55.978
-See you later.
-Okay.

44:56.143 --> 44:57.178
Later.

44:57.344 --> 45:00.814
This is the end,
so, what are we toasting to?

45:00.981 --> 45:02.790
To, uh, finding new jobs.

45:02.950 --> 45:05.328
Because it's only a matter of time
before they shut us down.

45:05.486 --> 45:08.160
-Hear, hear.
-Oh. Tc starting over.

45:12.493 --> 45:13.972
SAM:
Peter?

45:17.998 --> 45:19.500
It just doesn't make sense.

45:20.033 --> 45:22.513
She dies doing something
that she's done...

45:22.669 --> 45:25.582
...almost every day
for the last 15 years of her life.

45:26.340 --> 45:29.287
She said she didn't wanna do it.

45:29.443 --> 45:31.684
She said she wasn't ready.

45:34.148 --> 45:36.253
And I should have stopped her.

45:37.151 --> 45:38.892
I should have done something.
I should've--

45:39.052 --> 45:41.396
Peter, there wasn't anything
you could've done.

45:44.024 --> 45:45.560
How do you know?

45:46.393 --> 45:48.373
[GLASS SHATTERS]

45:50.764 --> 45:52.710
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

46:02.042 --> 46:05.888
Hello, Agent Block? This is Dennis.

46:06.046 --> 46:09.892
Yeah, Peter just freaked out
about something, I don't know what.

46:10.284 --> 46:11.558
Does that mean anything?

46:11.718 --> 46:14.130
[OVER PHONE]
You told me to call if I saw anything odd.

46:14.288 --> 46:19.829
I don't know yet, but thank you, Dennis,
and call me if you see anything strange.

46:19.993 --> 46:21.404
Stranger.

46:21.562 --> 46:25.874
Should we maybe have code names
for one another, do you think?

46:27.868 --> 46:29.472
Over and out.

46:30.537 --> 46:33.643
All right, ahem,
show me how this happened.

46:34.908 --> 46:36.046
I don't think I can.

46:36.210 --> 46:37.780
BLOCK:
What do you mean?

46:37.945 --> 46:43.554
I mean, I could try it a hundred times and
never re-create exactly what happened here.

46:44.952 --> 46:46.522
This is some freaky shit.

46:47.020 --> 46:48.328
[WATER DRIPS]

46:56.230 --> 46:57.300
[ISAAC SCREAMS]

46:57.464 --> 46:58.499
ISAAC:
God!

46:58.665 --> 47:01.202
[ISAAC GROANING]

47:03.337 --> 47:05.146
Oh, that actually felt great.

47:05.839 --> 47:07.147
[IN CHINESE]

47:07.474 --> 47:10.546
Oh, yeah. Awesome.

47:12.112 --> 47:13.489
Oh ....

47:15.082 --> 47:17.585
Wait. Are those things even sterilized?

47:17.751 --> 47:21.062
No, no. I'm not catching any diseases
unless I've earned them.

47:22.322 --> 47:23.494
[ISAAC SCOFFS]

47:28.996 --> 47:31.499
Wait a second. You understand that.

47:32.666 --> 47:34.646
You speak English.

47:35.903 --> 47:37.473
[CHUCKLING]

47:37.638 --> 47:38.946
Oh.

47:45.512 --> 47:46.991
All right, you know what?

47:47.147 --> 47:50.026
Let's do this.
Two billion people can't be Wang.

47:50.884 --> 47:53.023
I said Wang. You follow me?

47:53.186 --> 47:54.529
You get it, you're Chinese.

47:57.357 --> 47:58.392
[ISAAC YELPING]

47:58.559 --> 48:01.335
Ow, ow. Okay, it's in. it's definitely in.
Ow, okay, yes, it is in.

48:03.096 --> 48:04.734
How many of these are you gonna
put in me?

48:16.076 --> 48:17.111
[CELL PHONE BUZZING]

48:17.277 --> 48:21.350
Oh, uh, hey,
can you grab that for me? Thanks.

48:23.417 --> 48:24.862
Hey.

48:27.387 --> 48:29.264
That's not very nice, you know.

48:42.703 --> 48:44.580
Okay, your thumbs are kind of
in my eyes.

48:44.738 --> 48:46.411
I'm not gonna lie, it's a little annoying.

48:46.873 --> 48:50.377
Once again, Chinese lady,
I don't have a clue what you're saying.

48:51.311 --> 48:54.520
[IN ENGLISH]
Thirty minutes. You sleep.

49:05.392 --> 49:07.235
Sleep.

49:34.121 --> 49:35.327
Oh.

49:36.223 --> 49:39.397
Hey! Fire!

49:39.559 --> 49:41.436
Hello?!

49:41.595 --> 49:42.630
Hey!

49:43.363 --> 49:45.536
Hey! Hey!

49:45.699 --> 49:48.077
Hey, there's a fire in here!

49:48.635 --> 49:50.137
Hey, there's a fire!

49:50.971 --> 49:52.245
Get in here!

50:10.991 --> 50:12.368
[GASPS]

50:12.526 --> 50:15.530
[GRUNTING]

50:31.578 --> 50:34.582
[WHIMPERING]

50:47.160 --> 50:50.164
[CELL PHONE BUZZING]

50:52.999 --> 50:54.103
[GASPS]

50:55.068 --> 50:56.570
oh, sun.

50:57.037 --> 50:59.677
[SCREAMING]

51:05.078 --> 51:08.082
[SIGHING]

51:09.883 --> 51:11.089
[SCREAMS]

51:16.923 --> 51:18.869
SAM:
You should come with me.

51:19.326 --> 51:20.566
Tc Paris?

51:20.727 --> 51:24.368
Yeah, you know, you said it yourself.
Like, you're gonna have to start over.

51:25.932 --> 51:27.240
Start over with me.

51:29.669 --> 51:31.512
How many drinks have you had?

51:31.671 --> 51:34.618
Enough. Molly, I'm serious.

51:34.808 --> 51:38.950
Lack, you were right.
If I don't take the jab, I'll regret it.

51:40.447 --> 51:42.188
But I'm not willing to lose you.

51:42.349 --> 51:44.886
Why does it have to be
one or the other?

51:45.619 --> 51:47.257
I'm better when you're with me.

51:49.122 --> 51:52.103
Uh, guys, you're not gonna believe this.

52:05.572 --> 52:07.142
They're saying it was a freak accident.

52:07.307 --> 52:09.412
Yeah, raise your hand
if you believe that.

52:09.576 --> 52:12.750
Who dies during a massage? Seriously.

52:12.979 --> 52:15.050
PETER:
First Candice, new Isaac.

52:15.215 --> 52:17.058
It can't be a coincidence.

52:17.250 --> 52:18.957
It's not.

52:19.452 --> 52:20.897
Where are you going?

52:21.721 --> 52:23.723
NATHAN:
it's that creepy dude.

52:23.890 --> 52:26.700
SAM:
Why are you following us?

52:27.627 --> 52:29.004
Who are you?

52:30.130 --> 52:33.873
You were at the cemetery,
then the gym, new here.

52:34.868 --> 52:36.279
What are you doing?

52:36.436 --> 52:38.177
My job.

52:44.778 --> 52:47.258
[BLUDWORTH WHISTLING]

52:47.414 --> 52:49.291
SAM:
What's happening to us?

52:53.153 --> 52:55.463
What makes you think I know anything?

52:55.622 --> 52:56.794
SAM:
You warned us.

52:57.424 --> 53:00.337
At the memorial service.
You said Death didn't like to be cheated.

53:00.493 --> 53:03.531
It's just that I've seen this before.

53:04.197 --> 53:05.505
You've seen what?

53:05.665 --> 53:08.043
A lucky few survive a disaster.

53:08.201 --> 53:13.275
And then one by one,
Death comes for them all.

53:14.140 --> 53:17.212
You changed things on that bridge.

53:17.410 --> 53:22.484
There's a wrinkle in reality.
And that wrinkle is you.

53:22.649 --> 53:25.061
So, what, we're doomed to die?

53:25.552 --> 53:27.054
I mean, is that it?

53:27.420 --> 53:30.833
We just get our lives back,
so, what kind of fucked up karma is that?

53:30.991 --> 53:32.698
Are you saying that we can't stop this?

53:32.859 --> 53:35.635
You were supposed to die on that bridge.

53:36.162 --> 53:38.199
You're not supposed to be here.

53:39.032 --> 53:40.739
You shorted Death.

53:41.034 --> 53:43.708
So you let Death
have somebody else in your place...

53:43.870 --> 53:46.874
...and then you take their spot
in the realm of the living.

53:47.040 --> 53:50.886
All the days and years
that they have yet to live.

53:51.044 --> 53:54.651
And they take your place in death.

53:54.814 --> 53:56.384
Then the books are balanced.

53:56.549 --> 54:01.521
Wait a minute. We kill someone, we get
their life? Is that what you're telling me?

54:01.688 --> 54:03.998
I don't make the rules.

54:04.157 --> 54:10.199
I just clean up after the game is over.

54:17.504 --> 54:19.279
[ENGINE STARTS]

54:21.274 --> 54:25.086
Maybe that's why
Candice and Isaac are dead.

54:25.512 --> 54:28.755
They weren't supposed to survive,
and new it's coming after the rest of us.

54:29.215 --> 54:30.853
No.

54:31.017 --> 54:33.019
No, not all of us.

54:33.687 --> 54:35.530
Molly made it, she didn't die.

54:35.689 --> 54:37.032
What?

54:37.624 --> 54:42.573
Well, when I had that vision,
or premonition, or whatever it was...

54:43.763 --> 54:46.937
...I got you across
before the bridge collapsed.

54:47.100 --> 54:48.238
You survived.

54:48.635 --> 54:50.615
You saved her?

54:50.770 --> 54:54.445
Why, because you decided that she
deserved to live more than the rest of us?

54:54.607 --> 54:57.417
That's not what he's saying. I don't
deserve to live more than anyone.

54:57.577 --> 54:59.250
You deserve to live
more than Candice.

54:59.412 --> 55:00.584
Whoa, Peter, hang on.

55:00.747 --> 55:03.125
NATHAN:
No, look, guys, came on.

55:03.283 --> 55:05.263
You're not drinking the Kool-Aid,
are you?

55:05.418 --> 55:08.661
Killing people
to survive Death's list. Really?

55:09.789 --> 55:13.532
I may not know what's going on,
but it's not what that guy's selling.

55:14.060 --> 55:16.734
Yeah? What else is it, then?

55:20.967 --> 55:22.776
Shit.

55:22.936 --> 55:24.313
We need to tell Olivia.

55:24.738 --> 55:26.274
Come on.

55:30.310 --> 55:31.880
OLIVIA:
My farms are all signed.

55:32.045 --> 55:35.322
MAN: I see that it's been quite a while
since your first consultation.

55:35.482 --> 55:37.826
What made you decide
to take the leap today?

55:38.284 --> 55:42.255
Uh, well, a lot is going on in my life...

55:42.422 --> 55:45.631
...and I just don't wanna miss anything...

55:45.792 --> 55:47.100
...you know, important.

55:47.260 --> 55:48.933
Same reason I had it done myself.

55:49.095 --> 55:53.202
-Came on in back. Let's get you started.
-Okay.

55:54.234 --> 55:55.304
Oh.

55:59.806 --> 56:02.787
LEONOTTI: Yep, that's the first step.
You'll never need those again.

56:02.942 --> 56:04.080
[OLIVIA CHUCKLES]

56:06.212 --> 56:08.590
Here we are. Come on in.

56:20.126 --> 56:21.161
What's with these?

56:22.495 --> 56:24.975
Oh, just for some of
our younger patients.

56:26.733 --> 56:30.146
And, um, sometimes our older ones too.
Come on.

56:38.745 --> 56:40.554
[DRONING]

56:40.947 --> 56:42.358
What was that?

56:42.515 --> 56:44.119
Relax.

56:44.284 --> 56:47.128
You know, it lacks a lot worse
than it really is.

56:47.287 --> 56:51.599
Okay, I'm gently going to
position your head...

56:53.159 --> 56:54.832
...and I want you to tell me...

56:55.462 --> 56:57.840
...when this feels snug.

56:57.997 --> 56:59.408
I can't move my head.

56:59.566 --> 57:02.410
Perfect. Just what we want.

57:04.404 --> 57:06.350
There we go.

57:06.506 --> 57:10.147
Okay, now comes the fun part.
Here comes a drop.

57:10.877 --> 57:14.723
And you will feel a little numbness
in your eye...

57:14.881 --> 57:16.360
...which is a good thing.

57:32.398 --> 57:33.706
Deep breath.

57:38.338 --> 57:39.749
Relax.

57:46.513 --> 57:47.583
Very good.

57:53.953 --> 57:55.455
Thattagirl.

58:04.831 --> 58:06.174
There.

58:06.332 --> 58:09.074
That's not so bad, is it?

58:21.147 --> 58:22.649
Looks good.

58:29.822 --> 58:30.857
[CREAKING]

58:31.024 --> 58:33.129
-What was that?
-Just relax, Olivia.

58:33.293 --> 58:35.773
I'm just gonna enter some data into ....

58:40.066 --> 58:41.272
Dottie!

58:42.635 --> 58:44.012
Dot--

58:44.170 --> 58:46.844
Do you know what?
My assistant's given me an incomplete file.

58:47.006 --> 58:48.781
I'll be right back.

58:50.643 --> 58:52.884
OLIVIA:
Hold on, you're leaving?!

59:16.436 --> 59:19.440
[BEEPING]

59:23.209 --> 59:26.213
Is that supposed to be happening?!

59:32.986 --> 59:35.398
[BEEPING FASTER]

59:50.737 --> 59:53.650
[WHIMPERING]

59:55.808 --> 59:57.810
[MACHINE WHIRRING]

59:58.745 --> 01:00:01.191
[SCREAMING]

01:00:06.452 --> 01:00:07.760
Help me!

01:00:19.732 --> 01:00:21.405
Olivia Castle. Where is she?

01:00:21.567 --> 01:00:22.705
SAM:
She might be in danger.

01:00:22.869 --> 01:00:25.247
She's fine.
We do this kind of procedure all the time.

01:00:25.405 --> 01:00:27.351
[OLIVIA SCREAMING]

01:00:28.741 --> 01:00:29.845
[SOBBING]

01:00:33.279 --> 01:00:35.452
Help me!

01:00:36.182 --> 01:00:37.752
Help me!

01:00:38.518 --> 01:00:41.522
[SCREAMING]

01:00:56.317 --> 01:00:58.160
DOTTIE
This has never happened before.

01:00:58.319 --> 01:01:00.458
[DOTTIE & DETECTIVE
SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

01:01:02.891 --> 01:01:04.529
Sam.

01:01:05.593 --> 01:01:07.903
Stay with me tonight, please.

01:01:09.030 --> 01:01:10.873
Of course.

01:01:15.737 --> 01:01:17.808
Five different systems had to go wrong...

01:01:17.972 --> 01:01:21.852
...for that laser to fail us
so spectacularly. Five.

01:01:22.010 --> 01:01:23.751
What do you want from us?

01:01:23.912 --> 01:01:26.222
I want you to tell me
what you think is going on.

01:01:26.381 --> 01:01:29.089
Two deaths? Okay, all right.
That's a coincidence.

01:01:29.250 --> 01:01:32.163
Three? That's a pattern.

01:01:45.166 --> 01:01:46.645
Now...

01:01:47.368 --> 01:01:49.644
...I know you two didn't do this.

01:01:50.872 --> 01:01:52.146
All right?

01:01:53.541 --> 01:01:55.919
But I think you know something.

01:01:58.580 --> 01:01:59.752
What is it?

01:02:01.850 --> 01:02:04.296
We don't know anything.

01:02:04.919 --> 01:02:07.195
Take a guess.

01:02:13.027 --> 01:02:16.531
We think we weren't supposed to survive
on that bridge.

01:02:17.866 --> 01:02:18.901
What?

01:02:19.567 --> 01:02:23.879
And new something
is trying to set it right.

01:02:25.373 --> 01:02:27.114
"Something"?

01:02:28.910 --> 01:02:30.480
That's all you got?

01:02:30.678 --> 01:02:31.918
SAM:
Right now, yeah.

01:02:32.881 --> 01:02:37.557
But if you came up
with any other explanations, let us know.

01:02:40.221 --> 01:02:42.326
Thank you.

01:02:48.563 --> 01:02:50.338
"Something"

01:02:59.274 --> 01:03:00.446
Hey.

01:03:02.443 --> 01:03:03.854
Been up long?

01:03:05.980 --> 01:03:10.656
Uh, I don't know. I couldn't sleep.
I just kept thinking about the bridge.

01:03:14.455 --> 01:03:17.334
Sam, you can't do this to yourself.

01:03:17.492 --> 01:03:21.463
No. No, no, no. I was thinking about,
in the premonition...

01:03:22.297 --> 01:03:26.370
...we all get off the bus,
but the ground gave way and Candice fell.

01:03:27.735 --> 01:03:29.510
Then the bus tipped over.

01:03:30.638 --> 01:03:33.676
And Isaac, he never get off the bus.
He went with it.

01:03:33.842 --> 01:03:35.219
What are you getting at?

01:03:35.376 --> 01:03:38.516
I know that there was just
so much going on ....

01:03:39.514 --> 01:03:42.393
Lack, I know that I helped you across.

01:03:42.951 --> 01:03:45.761
Then I reached back for Olivia.

01:03:46.354 --> 01:03:48.698
But she didn't make it. She fell.

01:03:51.192 --> 01:03:53.968
So first was Candice.

01:03:54.128 --> 01:03:55.471
[SCREAMS]

01:03:56.798 --> 01:03:57.833
Then Isaac.

01:03:59.200 --> 01:04:00.270
Then Olivia.

01:04:00.435 --> 01:04:01.641
[SCREAMS]

01:04:01.803 --> 01:04:03.544
They're dying in order.

01:04:04.806 --> 01:04:06.547
Who dies after Olivia?

01:04:30.598 --> 01:04:31.941
[SIGHS]

01:04:42.010 --> 01:04:44.616
NATHAN [OVER PA]: Roy, would you come
to the control room, please?

01:04:44.779 --> 01:04:47.521
MAN: Uh-ch, Roy, that's the boss.
You in trouble, Roy.

01:05:04.065 --> 01:05:06.306
ROY: Okay, schoolboy,
what do you wanna talk to me about?

01:05:06.467 --> 01:05:09.277
NATHAN: What is with your timecard?
ROY: Let's talk about my timecard.

01:05:09.437 --> 01:05:11.917
You cut my hours,
which means you cut my pay!

01:05:12.073 --> 01:05:13.245
I cut everyone's hours, okay?

01:05:13.408 --> 01:05:16.514
Corporate has us operating at less than
50 percent until this thing blows over.

01:05:16.678 --> 01:05:18.680
My bookie ain't operating at 50 percent.

01:05:18.846 --> 01:05:21.383
-My dumb kid ain't operating at 50 percent.
-Ray.

01:05:21.549 --> 01:05:24.621
My ex-wife, she's taking 50 percent,
so I'll tell you what I'm gonna do.

01:05:24.786 --> 01:05:25.924
No, we gotta move, man.

01:05:26.087 --> 01:05:29.432
ROY: Hey, I'm not going anywhere. Hey!
NATHAN: Look, we gotta move! Gotta move!

01:05:29.590 --> 01:05:30.898
We gotta move now!

01:05:32.727 --> 01:05:35.139
[ROY GRUNTS THEN SCREAMS]

01:05:40.969 --> 01:05:43.245
NATHAN:
Roy! You okay down there?

01:05:47.942 --> 01:05:49.444
-Hey, Dennis?
DENNIS: Hey.

01:05:51.612 --> 01:05:53.592
They're closing us down.

01:05:53.748 --> 01:05:55.022
They're shutting down the plant?

01:05:55.183 --> 01:05:59.495
Not the plant, just us.
Just sales and administration.

01:05:59.654 --> 01:06:01.327
Can you believe it? Us?

01:06:01.489 --> 01:06:03.662
It's the factory guys
that usually get laid off.

01:06:03.825 --> 01:06:05.361
Not us, we're supposed to be safe.

01:06:05.526 --> 01:06:07.904
Yeah, Dennis, we get bigger problems.

01:06:08.763 --> 01:06:10.504
Olivia and Isaac are dead.

01:06:11.499 --> 01:06:12.603
Who's Isaac?

01:06:12.767 --> 01:06:15.839
Isaac Palmer, tech support.

01:06:16.904 --> 01:06:18.178
Wasn't he dead already?

01:06:18.339 --> 01:06:19.716
No, Dennis.

01:06:19.907 --> 01:06:25.220
Listen, it's going to happen to us too
if we don't do something about it.

01:06:25.847 --> 01:06:29.192
Yeah, I understand.
Listen, it's called survivor's guilt.

01:06:29.350 --> 01:06:33.457
No. No, guilt doesn't kill you.

01:06:33.621 --> 01:06:35.567
Obviously, you've never met my in-laws.

01:06:35.723 --> 01:06:37.532
I'm not fucking around here, Dennis.

01:06:37.992 --> 01:06:39.562
Anyone could be next.

01:06:39.727 --> 01:06:42.367
It could be you. Understand?

01:06:42.530 --> 01:06:44.009
Nobody's safe.

01:06:44.165 --> 01:06:45.701
What are you talking about?

01:06:48.002 --> 01:06:50.710
We weren't supposed to survive
that bridge collapse.

01:06:50.872 --> 01:06:53.751
And so new it's kill or be killed.

01:06:54.342 --> 01:06:56.515
You get that, Dennis?

01:06:57.645 --> 01:06:58.680
Whatever.

01:06:58.846 --> 01:07:01.690
I warned you.
Do whatever you wanna do.

01:07:03.718 --> 01:07:04.822
[DOOR CLOSES]

01:07:05.520 --> 01:07:07.227
I will.

01:07:12.026 --> 01:07:14.336
Hey, Agent Black, it's Dennis. Um--

01:07:14.495 --> 01:07:18.409
Listen, Pete just came in here
and he's just completely lost it.

01:07:18.566 --> 01:07:21.445
He's yelling about "kill or be killed."

01:07:21.602 --> 01:07:24.549
Oh, yeah,
it definitely sounded like a threat.

01:07:41.489 --> 01:07:42.593
What happened?

01:07:42.757 --> 01:07:45.704
NATHAN: I don't know. I don't know.
It just happened so fast.

01:07:45.860 --> 01:07:48.568
-Nathan. Are you okay?
-Yeah.

01:07:48.729 --> 01:07:52.404
-We heard, and we thought--
-No. No, uh, I'm good.

01:07:53.534 --> 01:07:54.774
Did you kill him?

01:07:55.136 --> 01:07:56.274
What?

01:07:56.437 --> 01:07:59.043
No. No, I just--

01:07:59.207 --> 01:08:02.086
It was just timing, you know?
He get in the way and--

01:08:02.243 --> 01:08:03.551
No, you did, didn't you?

01:08:03.711 --> 01:08:07.090
You saw it coming, and then you tack
his life. You put him in the way.

01:08:07.248 --> 01:08:08.886
No, I didn't really do anything.

01:08:09.050 --> 01:08:11.894
-Tell us the truth: Did you or didn't you?
-Hey, Peter, calm down.

01:08:12.053 --> 01:08:13.430
Did you or didn't you?

01:08:16.256 --> 01:08:18.294
Did you or didn't you?

01:08:19.227 --> 01:08:22.140
Yes. I think I did.

01:08:22.964 --> 01:08:24.238
I killed him.

01:08:25.133 --> 01:08:28.307
So if the theory works,
then you traded spots.

01:08:28.469 --> 01:08:32.144
He should have your death,
and you should have his years.

01:08:32.907 --> 01:08:34.180
How do we know for sure?

01:08:34.341 --> 01:08:36.252
I think there's an order to these deaths.

01:08:37.645 --> 01:08:40.626
They mirror the order everyone died in
on the bridge.

01:08:40.781 --> 01:08:42.555
Then who would be next?

01:08:44.417 --> 01:08:46.658
Who wants to be first to tell me
what the hell happened?

01:08:47.121 --> 01:08:48.156
Who is it, Sam?

01:08:48.322 --> 01:08:49.357
Who's what?

01:08:50.992 --> 01:08:53.801
[ALL GASPING]

01:08:54.662 --> 01:08:57.165
Dennis! It was Dennis.

01:08:57.631 --> 01:08:59.612
No shit.

01:09:00.635 --> 01:09:02.376
MAN:
Jesus.

01:09:05.640 --> 01:09:07.483
Why are you fighting me on this?

01:09:07.642 --> 01:09:10.020
You're not seriously going to work,
are you?

01:09:10.178 --> 01:09:14.490
Molly, Isaac died on a massage table.

01:09:14.649 --> 01:09:17.323
If Death is gonna came for me,
I don't think it matters where I am.

01:09:17.484 --> 01:09:19.225
You have to do something.

01:09:19.386 --> 01:09:22.129
-What, kill someone so I can live?
-No, of course not.

01:09:22.890 --> 01:09:25.029
We'll just have to
figure something else out.

01:09:25.193 --> 01:09:27.264
I have figured it out.

01:09:27.728 --> 01:09:30.709
Something saved me on that bridge.

01:09:30.865 --> 01:09:32.707
Maybe it doesn't want me to die.

01:09:35.036 --> 01:09:36.515
Maybe.

01:09:36.671 --> 01:09:39.550
We can't live our lives in fear, Moll.

01:09:41.908 --> 01:09:46.220
So if it happens tomorrow,
or 50 years from now, whatever.

01:09:46.380 --> 01:09:48.587
As long as we're together...

01:09:49.850 --> 01:09:51.055
...I'll be okay.

01:09:53.754 --> 01:09:56.598
Right? Why don't you came by
after my shift...

01:09:56.757 --> 01:09:58.862
...and I'll make you
a nice late dinner, okay?

01:10:07.635 --> 01:10:09.012
All right, give me this.

01:10:12.240 --> 01:10:14.117
[SIGHS]

01:10:14.275 --> 01:10:16.277
[CHATTERING]

01:10:17.945 --> 01:10:20.221
WOMAN: Excuse me.
We don't have to wait for them, do we?

01:10:20.381 --> 01:10:22.691
HOSTESS: I'll let you know.
WOMAN: Okay, thank you.

01:10:22.850 --> 01:10:25.330
[TERRY POISON'S "GIRL ON THE RUN"
PLAYING ON SPEAKERS]

01:10:25.486 --> 01:10:27.830
To the girl on the run

01:10:27.989 --> 01:10:31.027
[SINGER SINGING IN FRENCH]

01:10:38.399 --> 01:10:39.878
COOK 1:
Veal's ready, take it out.

01:10:40.034 --> 01:10:42.105
Samuel. Get to work on the bourguignon.

01:10:42.270 --> 01:10:43.749
[SPEAKING IN FRENCH]

01:10:50.444 --> 01:10:51.650
Whoa.

01:10:52.079 --> 01:10:53.114
COOK 2:
Pan coming through.

01:10:54.749 --> 01:10:56.422
COOK 3:
Whoa, watch yourself.

01:11:07.161 --> 01:11:09.505
MANAGER: Okay. Meat's in. Pick it up, eh?
COOK 4: Yes, sir.

01:11:20.374 --> 01:11:22.047
Whoa.

01:11:22.209 --> 01:11:24.086
That could've been ugly, huh? Ha, ha.

01:11:24.245 --> 01:11:26.885
Yeah. Could've been.

01:11:31.919 --> 01:11:33.296
Vincent, speed it up, okay?

01:11:40.628 --> 01:11:41.902
SAM:
Whoa, hey!

01:11:42.063 --> 01:11:43.098
[SPUTTERING]

01:11:57.378 --> 01:11:58.413
[SIGHS]

01:12:05.486 --> 01:12:07.488
CHEF:
Hey, clean that grate.

01:12:15.963 --> 01:12:18.967
-Just met your girlfriend.
-Oh.

01:12:19.133 --> 01:12:22.046
Are you sure it's okay
if I make her a little something?

01:12:22.670 --> 01:12:24.707
Make sure to clean up afterward.

01:12:24.872 --> 01:12:27.648
I will, of course. Thank you.

01:12:28.909 --> 01:12:30.286
And, chef ....

01:12:30.444 --> 01:12:31.718
[SPEAKS IN FRENCH]

01:12:31.879 --> 01:12:33.756
The apprenticeship.

01:12:33.914 --> 01:12:36.417
If the offer still stands...

01:12:36.584 --> 01:12:37.927
...I'd like to take it.

01:12:39.587 --> 01:12:41.089
It's yours.

01:12:45.693 --> 01:12:48.833
[WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER RADIO]

01:12:55.803 --> 01:12:57.282
SAM:
Okay, no more suspense.

01:12:57.438 --> 01:12:58.917
[MOLLY CHUCKLES]

01:12:59.073 --> 01:13:01.110
What you've been waiting for.

01:13:02.877 --> 01:13:05.357
Wow. You're gonna help me
with this, right?

01:13:05.513 --> 01:13:06.958
Yeah, sure, if you want me to--

01:13:07.114 --> 01:13:08.616
No? You don't want me to...?

01:13:09.417 --> 01:13:10.589
So how's your French?

01:13:11.085 --> 01:13:13.326
Heh. Terrible.

01:13:13.487 --> 01:13:17.162
Oh, good. Well, then,
we can be terrible together.

01:13:17.324 --> 01:13:20.533
-why?
-I tack the internship.

01:13:20.694 --> 01:13:24.608
What? Sam, that's amazing.

01:13:27.968 --> 01:13:29.777
I'm so proud of you.

01:13:46.954 --> 01:13:49.696
-Peter.
-Hey.

01:13:51.492 --> 01:13:54.530
You okay, man?
You lack a little, uh, upset.

01:13:54.695 --> 01:13:58.643
Yeah. Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Just a rough couple days.

01:13:59.333 --> 01:14:02.007
Yeah. Yeah, for everyone.

01:14:02.970 --> 01:14:04.847
For some more than others.

01:14:05.639 --> 01:14:07.084
Do you mind if I came in?

01:14:07.241 --> 01:14:09.585
Oh, yeah, of course. Yeah, came in.

01:14:15.249 --> 01:14:16.728
Here, have a seat.

01:14:17.585 --> 01:14:19.155
Thanks.

01:14:23.324 --> 01:14:24.598
Hey, Peter.

01:14:25.726 --> 01:14:27.535
Hi, Molly.

01:14:42.343 --> 01:14:46.155
Peter, can I get you anything to eat?
I can make you up some pasta.

01:14:46.747 --> 01:14:50.285
Uh, no. No, no, no. I'm good.
Uh, thank you.

01:14:51.785 --> 01:14:53.628
Uh, I'm sorry. I just thought--

01:14:53.787 --> 01:14:56.358
It's good that you're here.
You shouldn't be alone right now.

01:14:56.991 --> 01:14:59.437
Yeah, you know,
I'm surprised I'm here at all.

01:15:00.861 --> 01:15:02.306
Uh ....

01:15:02.463 --> 01:15:04.272
Still alive, I mean.

01:15:04.431 --> 01:15:05.774
I'm next to go, right?

01:15:07.101 --> 01:15:08.774
It's me and then you, isn't it?

01:15:11.572 --> 01:15:16.419
Anyways, uh, I was up all last night,
you know...

01:15:16.577 --> 01:15:19.751
...thinking about if I could really do it.

01:15:20.381 --> 01:15:24.193
-Do what?
-Take someone else's life.

01:15:24.351 --> 01:15:29.596
If I could actually kill some stranger,
replace their life with my own.

01:15:30.558 --> 01:15:32.469
And I thought about it.

01:15:33.260 --> 01:15:35.262
And I convinced myself that...

01:15:36.630 --> 01:15:38.166
...yeah, I could.

01:15:40.801 --> 01:15:43.247
So I went on a walk.

01:15:43.404 --> 01:15:46.146
You know, nowhere in particular...

01:15:46.307 --> 01:15:49.220
...but every couple of minutes,
an opportunity would just present itself.

01:15:49.376 --> 01:15:52.152
Heh. Like clockwork.

01:15:52.580 --> 01:15:55.652
I could just grab somebody
and pull them into an alley.

01:15:56.250 --> 01:15:59.823
Or just shave somebody off a curb
into traffic.

01:16:00.588 --> 01:16:02.033
You know?

01:16:02.856 --> 01:16:04.130
It'd be real easy.

01:16:07.194 --> 01:16:09.435
Peter, what did you do?

01:16:17.137 --> 01:16:19.583
-Did you...?
-No, I didn't.

01:16:22.476 --> 01:16:24.547
I couldn't.

01:16:24.712 --> 01:16:26.555
I realized that...

01:16:26.714 --> 01:16:29.627
...I couldn't kill somebody
that didn't deserve to die.

01:16:31.719 --> 01:16:35.428
And I thought about Candice,
and I thought, "Wait a minute.

01:16:36.457 --> 01:16:39.370
Candice didn't deserve to die.

01:16:41.362 --> 01:16:44.104
Olivia didn't. Dennis didn't.

01:16:44.898 --> 01:16:46.468
I don't."

01:16:48.369 --> 01:16:49.677
Do I?

01:16:49.903 --> 01:16:52.076
No, of course you don't.

01:16:55.009 --> 01:16:56.454
Well...

01:16:57.611 --> 01:17:03.721
...none of us deserve to die,
then why is it...

01:17:05.019 --> 01:17:08.000
...that you deserve to live, Molly?

01:17:09.923 --> 01:17:11.197
You said it yourself...

01:17:12.393 --> 01:17:13.565
...you don't.

01:17:16.430 --> 01:17:17.602
[GUNSHOT]

01:17:19.266 --> 01:17:20.677
Go!

01:17:21.402 --> 01:17:25.976
Repeat, shots fired.
Requesting backup. 1026 Washington.

01:17:26.707 --> 01:17:30.120
Hide and I'll distract him.
When you can, go.

01:17:32.212 --> 01:17:33.691
PETER:
Not done yet, Sam.

01:17:36.350 --> 01:17:37.658
Where is she?

01:17:39.687 --> 01:17:43.464
-Where is she?!
-I'm not gonna let you hurt her, Peter.

01:17:43.657 --> 01:17:45.466
You're gonna have to kill me first.

01:17:45.659 --> 01:17:47.832
Well, that doesn't do me any good.
Heh, heh.

01:17:47.995 --> 01:17:49.235
Death's after you too.

01:17:49.396 --> 01:17:51.774
This is crazy, Peter. Don't do this.

01:17:52.933 --> 01:17:56.540
Just think for a minute, all right?

01:17:56.704 --> 01:17:58.308
You are not a killer.

01:17:59.673 --> 01:18:01.311
I don't wanna kill anybody, Sam.

01:18:04.678 --> 01:18:05.884
I don't wanna die yet either.

01:18:06.046 --> 01:18:07.457
[BOTH GRUNT]

01:18:12.753 --> 01:18:15.097
Heh. it's not your time yet.

01:18:24.098 --> 01:18:26.271
Don't worry, Molly...

01:18:28.435 --> 01:18:30.005
...I didn't kill him.

01:18:32.439 --> 01:18:36.148
But I didn't need to, Molly...

01:18:37.244 --> 01:18:41.317
...because Death
is gonna do that for me.

01:18:41.782 --> 01:18:44.160
Doesn't mean I can't help it.

01:18:46.120 --> 01:18:47.827
That's it.

01:19:29.530 --> 01:19:32.773
-Are you okay? What's going on?
-it's Peter. He has a gun.

01:19:32.933 --> 01:19:34.435
[GUNFIRE]

01:19:38.005 --> 01:19:39.678
Oh, my God.

01:19:43.076 --> 01:19:44.783
You killed him.

01:19:52.152 --> 01:19:53.654
It's Sam's turn.

01:19:59.726 --> 01:20:02.206
MOLLY:
Peter, just go.

01:20:02.596 --> 01:20:05.805
You have Block's life, you're safe now.

01:20:06.667 --> 01:20:08.146
Please.

01:20:08.368 --> 01:20:10.245
I'm sorry, Molly.

01:20:12.439 --> 01:20:15.181
But you just witnessed the murder
of a federal agent.

01:20:17.845 --> 01:20:22.351
And I'm not gonna spend
the life I just earned in prison.

01:20:23.483 --> 01:20:24.689
[MOLLY SCREAMS]

01:20:28.121 --> 01:20:31.364
[BOTH GRUNTING]

01:20:33.827 --> 01:20:36.433
Molly, go! Go get help!

01:21:04.224 --> 01:21:06.602
You son of a bitch!

01:21:44.631 --> 01:21:47.874
Tell Candice I love her.

01:21:48.235 --> 01:21:49.270
Peter.

01:22:15.228 --> 01:22:18.402
It's gone. You killed him.

01:22:19.199 --> 01:22:21.008
So does that mean I get Block's life?

01:22:21.835 --> 01:22:23.280
[MOLLY SCREAMS]

01:22:26.006 --> 01:22:27.508
Yeah.

01:22:28.208 --> 01:22:30.119
I guess I do.

01:22:46.093 --> 01:22:47.595
Do you mind if I take the window seat?

01:22:47.995 --> 01:22:51.033
-You're gonna make me sit in the middle?
-Uh-huh.

01:22:51.198 --> 01:22:53.371
SAM: I'm like twice your size.
-Not really.

01:22:53.533 --> 01:22:55.535
-All right.
MAN 1: Sit down.

01:22:55.702 --> 01:22:58.046
MAN 2: I'll remove him.
GUY: Fuck you. I'll remove myself.

01:22:58.205 --> 01:22:59.411
GIRL:
Get off him!

01:22:59.573 --> 01:23:00.847
Settle down!

01:23:01.008 --> 01:23:03.887
-Came on, Browning! Come on, you punk!
-Get off the plane!

01:23:04.044 --> 01:23:06.524
Get off the plane. You don't understand!

01:23:06.680 --> 01:23:08.387
LEWTON:
Everybody just stay where you are.

01:23:10.684 --> 01:23:14.325
-What's all that about?
-I have no idea.

01:23:14.488 --> 01:23:17.594
PILOT [OVER PA]: Ladies and gentlemen,
we'll be pulling away from the gate as--

01:23:17.758 --> 01:23:19.101
[STATIC CRACKLES OVER PA]

01:23:23.697 --> 01:23:24.801
MOLLY:
Here we go.

01:23:24.998 --> 01:23:27.535
WOMAN 1 [OVER PA]: The cabin lights
have been dimmed for takeoff.

01:23:27.701 --> 01:23:30.375
[MAN 3 SPEAKING IN FRENCH OVER PA]

01:23:50.590 --> 01:23:52.570
[KANSAS' "DUST IN THE WIND"
PLAYING ON HEADPHONES]

01:23:52.726 --> 01:23:55.332
With curiosity

01:23:56.730 --> 01:24:00.200
Dust in the wind

01:24:05.372 --> 01:24:06.680
[MOLLY GASPS]

01:24:12.412 --> 01:24:13.652
Sorry about that.

01:24:15.982 --> 01:24:18.258
WOMAN 2:
Oh, excuse me.

01:24:18.418 --> 01:24:23.094
Those passengers who got off the plane
earlier, what was that all about?

01:24:23.256 --> 01:24:25.930
FLIGHT ATTENDANT: A kid had
a panic attack and wanted off the plane.

01:24:26.259 --> 01:24:28.205
Said he had some kind of vision.

01:24:29.062 --> 01:24:30.405
No.

01:24:32.499 --> 01:24:33.603
Oh, my God!

01:24:35.902 --> 01:24:37.848
[PASSENGERS SCREAMING]

01:24:38.538 --> 01:24:39.573
Sam.

01:24:59.826 --> 01:25:01.305
[SCREAMING]

01:25:05.265 --> 01:25:08.041
[MOLLY SCREAMING]

01:25:08.201 --> 01:25:09.339
SAM:
I get you!

01:25:11.538 --> 01:25:14.485
-Sam!
-Molly, hold on!

01:25:16.076 --> 01:25:17.111
No!

01:25:17.277 --> 01:25:18.585
[SCREAMS]

01:25:19.146 --> 01:25:20.819
No!

01:25:23.116 --> 01:25:25.460
[SAM SCREAMING IN SLOW MOTION]

01:25:34.828 --> 01:25:36.865
[KANSAS' "DUST IN THE WIND"
PLAYING ON SPEAKERS]

01:25:37.030 --> 01:25:39.874
[CROWD CHATTERING]

01:25:45.172 --> 01:25:46.708
Nice of you to come, Nathan.

01:25:46.873 --> 01:25:49.149
I know Ray
wasn't the easiest guy to work with.

01:25:50.210 --> 01:25:51.621
You know.

01:25:51.778 --> 01:25:53.883
I still can't believe he's gone, though.

01:25:54.047 --> 01:25:56.527
Yeah. Yeah, no kidding.

01:25:56.683 --> 01:25:57.957
I guess it was for the best.

01:25:59.419 --> 01:26:00.454
What do you mean?

01:26:00.620 --> 01:26:03.794
Company did an autopsy
for insurance purposes.

01:26:03.957 --> 01:26:07.029
Turns out Roy had an enlarged
blood vessel in his brain so big...

01:26:07.194 --> 01:26:10.471
...it was about to burst.
They said he'd be dead any day now.

01:26:10.630 --> 01:26:12.940
[OVER SPEAKERS]
Nothing lasts forever but the ....

01:26:13.099 --> 01:26:14.737
Any day?

01:26:15.702 --> 01:26:16.737
Life's a bitch.

01:26:16.903 --> 01:26:18.712
Dust in the wind

01:26:30.917 --> 01:26:32.328
[SCREAMS]

01:26:34.487 --> 01:26:35.625
[TIRES SCREECH]

01:26:39.659 --> 01:26:40.797
[GROANS]

01:26:40.994 --> 01:26:42.064
[GROANS]

01:27:11.224 --> 01:27:12.294
[MUFFLED SCREAM]

01:27:29.376 --> 01:27:30.616
[SCREAMS]

01:27:46.126 --> 01:27:47.764
[YELLS]

01:27:59.139 --> 01:28:02.416
BLUDWORTH:
You all just be careful now.

